&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The correct answer is:&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;Mixed economy.&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After India gained independence in 1947, the leaders of the nation were faced with the challenge of designing an economic system that would align with the country&amp;#39;s social, political, and economic goals. India adopted a mixed economy model, combining features of both capitalism and socialism, to address its unique needs and aspirations.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Definition of Mixed Economy:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A mixed economy is an economic system that incorporates elements of both capitalism (private ownership) and socialism (state ownership) to balance the benefits of both systems.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It allows co-existence of the public sector, controlled by the government, and the private sector, owned by individuals or corporations.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why India Opted for a Mixed Economy:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;India was a newly independent nation with diverse challenges like poverty, illiteracy, and lack of industrialization. A mixed economy provided a balanced approach to address these issues.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The model aimed to reduce economic disparities by encouraging government intervention while allowing private enterprises to flourish.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The mixed economy was seen as a way to promote social welfare, economic growth, and equitable distribution of resources.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Features of India&amp;rsquo;s Mixed Economy:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Public Sector:&lt;/strong&gt; The government took control of key industries such as railways, defense, and heavy industries to ensure strategic development and public welfare.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Private Sector:&lt;/strong&gt; Private enterprises were encouraged in areas like consumer goods, agriculture, and small-scale industries to promote entrepreneurship and economic dynamism.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Planning System:&lt;/strong&gt; India adopted a planned economic approach through Five-Year Plans, guided by the Planning Commission, to systematically allocate resources and set national priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Regulation:&lt;/strong&gt; The government introduced policies and regulations to prevent monopolies, control inflation, and ensure fair trade practices.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Impacts of the Mixed Economy Model:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It facilitated industrial growth and infrastructure development, especially in the public sector.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Encouraged private sector participation, leading to job creation and innovation.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Helped address social challenges like poverty and unemployment through targeted welfare programs.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Historical Context:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;India&amp;rsquo;s mixed economy approach was influenced by leaders like Jawaharlal Nehru, who believed in a balance between state control and market forces.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Soviet Union&amp;rsquo;s socialist model and Western capitalist systems served as inspirations for crafting India&amp;#39;s unique economic framework.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Challenges of a Mixed Economy:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Excessive government control in certain sectors led to inefficiencies and bureaucratic delays.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The license-permit raj system restricted private sector growth and innovation during the early decades.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Over time, economic liberalization in the 1990s reduced state control and paved the way for a more market-driven approach.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Current Scenario:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;India continues to be a mixed economy but has shifted towards greater privatization and market-driven policies since the 1991 economic reforms.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The government still plays a significant role in sectors like healthcare, education, and infrastructure development to ensure social equity.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

The correct answer is option 1,Key Points:
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Ganga Basin is the most populous river basin in India, supporting a significant portion of the country&amp;#39;s population.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The basin covers approximately 1 million square kilometers and spans across 11 states, including Uttar Pradesh, Bihar, West Bengal, and Uttarakhand.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is home to major cities such as Delhi, Kanpur, Lucknow, Allahabad, Varanasi, Patna, and Kolkata.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The fertile alluvial plains of the Ganga Basin make it an agricultural hub, contributing to high population density.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Ganga River provides water for irrigation, drinking, and industrial purposes, further boosting population concentration in the region.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
Additional Information:

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;River Basin:&lt;/strong&gt; A geographical area drained by a river and its tributaries, forming a crucial unit for water management and planning.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Alluvial Plains:&lt;/strong&gt; Fertile flatlands formed by the deposition of sediment from rivers, ideal for agriculture and human settlement.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Population Density:&lt;/strong&gt; The number of people living per unit area; the Ganga Basin has one of the highest population densities in the world.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Urbanization:&lt;/strong&gt; The Ganga Basin hosts several metropolitan cities, contributing to economic activities and increasing population concentration.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Environmental Challenges:&lt;/strong&gt; The Ganga Basin faces issues such as pollution, deforestation, and over-extraction of resources due to the high population and industrial activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);&quot;&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;tropical belts&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;include desert and semidesert landscapes on the continents and of high water temperatures and high salinity in the ocean.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;There are two important latitudes&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;23&amp;frac12;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);&quot;&gt;&amp;deg;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;North&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the tropic of&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Cancer&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;23&amp;frac12;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);&quot;&gt;&amp;deg;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;South&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the tropic of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Capricorn.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;area&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;lying between these&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;two tropics&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;is&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;known as the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;tropical region.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus, it is clear that&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;f&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;rom the tropic of Cancer to the tropic of Capricorn&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;extension of the tropical belt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;​&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The region lying&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;5&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;to&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;10 degrees&lt;/span&gt;, north and south of Tropic of cancer and the Tropic of Capricorn is known as&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subtropical Region.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Some of the areas that lie in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subtropical region&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;across the globe are
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;​&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;The Northern Part of India&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Parts of South America&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Certain parts of Northern Australia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; ​&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;The region between&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;5&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;to&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;10&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;degree is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;near the Equator&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is called the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Equatorial Region&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;With reference to the Age of Consent Act, 1891 consider the following statements :&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. It was Behramji Malabari, a Parsi reformer from Bombay, who advocated for this legislation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. The Act was supported by the extremist wing led by Bal Gangadhar Tilak.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Which of the above statements is/are correct?&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;h5 data-end=&quot;179&quot; data-start=&quot;64&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 2&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;

&lt;h5 data-end=&quot;179&quot; data-start=&quot;64&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;h5 data-end=&quot;179&quot; data-start=&quot;64&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-end=&quot;177&quot; data-start=&quot;69&quot;&gt;Statement 1: It was Behramji Malabari, a Parsi reformer from Bombay, who advocated for this legislation-&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong data-end=&quot;194&quot; data-start=&quot;182&quot;&gt;Correct.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;366&quot; data-start=&quot;197&quot;&gt;
		&lt;h5&gt;&lt;strong data-end=&quot;220&quot; data-start=&quot;199&quot;&gt;Behramji Malabari&lt;/strong&gt;, a Parsi social reformer, played a crucial role in advocating for raising the &lt;strong data-end=&quot;363&quot; data-start=&quot;299&quot;&gt;age of consent for marriage and sexual intercourse for girls&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/h5&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;488&quot; data-start=&quot;367&quot;&gt;
		&lt;h5&gt;He actively wrote about &lt;strong data-end=&quot;443&quot; data-start=&quot;393&quot;&gt;child marriage and the poor condition of women&lt;/strong&gt; in India, influencing British authorities.&lt;/h5&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;676&quot; data-start=&quot;489&quot;&gt;
		&lt;h5&gt;His efforts, along with those of reformers like &lt;strong data-end=&quot;552&quot; data-start=&quot;539&quot;&gt;Rukhmabai&lt;/strong&gt;, led to the passage of the &lt;strong data-end=&quot;608&quot; data-start=&quot;580&quot;&gt;Age of Consent Act, 1891&lt;/strong&gt;, which &lt;strong data-end=&quot;675&quot; data-start=&quot;616&quot;&gt;raised the age of consent for girls from 10 to 12 years&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/h5&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;h5 data-end=&quot;773&quot; data-start=&quot;678&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-end=&quot;771&quot; data-start=&quot;683&quot;&gt;Statement 2: The Act was supported by the extremist wing led by Bal Gangadhar Tilak-&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong data-end=&quot;790&quot; data-start=&quot;776&quot;&gt;Incorrect.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;895&quot; data-start=&quot;793&quot;&gt;
		&lt;h5&gt;&lt;strong data-end=&quot;892&quot; data-start=&quot;795&quot;&gt;Bal Gangadhar Tilak and the extremist faction of the Indian National Congress opposed the Act&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/h5&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;1010&quot; data-start=&quot;896&quot;&gt;
		&lt;h5&gt;They saw it as &lt;strong data-end=&quot;979&quot; data-start=&quot;913&quot;&gt;British interference in Indian social and religious traditions&lt;/strong&gt;, particularly Hindu customs.&lt;/h5&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;1144&quot; data-start=&quot;1011&quot;&gt;
		&lt;h5&gt;Tilak argued that &lt;strong data-end=&quot;1141&quot; data-start=&quot;1031&quot;&gt;social reforms should come from within Indian society rather than being imposed by the colonial government&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/h5&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;h5 data-end=&quot;1233&quot; data-is-last-node=&quot;&quot; data-is-only-node=&quot;&quot; data-start=&quot;1146&quot;&gt;Hence, only &lt;strong data-end=&quot;1183&quot; data-start=&quot;1157&quot;&gt;Statement 1 is correct&lt;/strong&gt;, making option &lt;strong data-end=&quot;1213&quot; data-start=&quot;1199&quot;&gt;(2) Only 1&lt;/strong&gt; the correct answer.&lt;/h5&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1995&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;National Legal Service Day&amp;nbsp;came into force on 9th November &lt;strong&gt;1995&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Day is celebrated to make people aware of the various provisions under the &lt;strong&gt;Legal Services Authorities Act and the right&lt;/strong&gt; of the litigants.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;It was first started by the &lt;strong&gt;Supreme Court of India&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The day is observed to commemorate the enactment of the Legal Services Authorities Act and to create awareness about the various provisions related to the act.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Persons with disabilities have equal rights, and the government should make possible their full participation in society,&amp;nbsp;the government has to provide &lt;strong&gt;free education and integrate children with disabilities&lt;/strong&gt; into mainstream schools, this law was passed in&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;1995&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Aziz Mushabber Ahmadi&lt;/strong&gt; was the &lt;strong&gt;26th Chief Justice&lt;/strong&gt; of India in &lt;strong&gt;1995.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Constitution &lt;strong&gt;77th amendment Act, 1995&lt;/strong&gt; was introduced in the Lok Sabha on &lt;strong&gt;May 31st, 1995&lt;/strong&gt;. This Act extended &lt;strong&gt;reservations for promotion in employment for Scheduled Castes and Tribes&lt;/strong&gt; (SCs and STs).&lt;br /&gt;
	&lt;span id=&quot;cke_bm_3230C&quot; style=&quot;display: none;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Samudragupta.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Prayag Prashasti was an article composed by Harisena&lt;/strong&gt;, the court poet of Emperor Samudragupta of the Gupta dynasty.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This&lt;strong&gt; inscription was engraved on the Ashoka pillar brought from Kaushambi by Samudragupta in 200 AD.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It &lt;strong&gt;describes the kingdoms that fought with Samudragupta and were defeated and subordinated to him.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Apart from this, Samudragupta had also inscribed Eran Prashasti, Gaya Copper Rule articles, etc., at different places.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;According to this prashasti, &lt;strong&gt;Samudragupta had expanded his empire well.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The inscriptions of Prayagraj show that &lt;strong&gt;Samudragupta started his conquest by defeating nine rulers of Aryavarta in northern India, which included Nagasena, Achyuta, Ganapati etc.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Through these victories, Samudra Gupta established his power over Madhya Pradesh or the Ganges Yamuna Doab.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;He completely &lt;strong&gt;abolished these 9 rulers &lt;/strong&gt;because it was not possible for him to move forward without completely defeating and eradicating the competing states of the central region.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
